{"timestamp":"2026-02-13T00:56:10.596Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"item_completed","thread_id":"019c5477-7f81-75e2-9eec-9da13c5b03b7","turn_id":"019c547c-5889-7581-979c-ca1eb13ba4dd","item":{"type":"Plan","id":"019c547c-5889-7581-979c-ca1eb13ba4dd-plan","text":"# Open-Source Release Readiness Plan (README, Collab Docs, Windows/Linux Support)\n\n**Summary**\n- Add a simple, obvious `README.md` with clear value prop, usage, install, and support info.\n- Add standard collaborator docs: `CONTRIBUTING.md`, `CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md`, `SECURITY.md`.\n- Extend installer and runtime paths to fully support Linux and Windows.\n- Expand install docs, including the existing macOS curl command and Windows PowerShell + optional `winget` guidance.\n\n## 1. Documentation Updates\n\n### 1.1 Create `README.md`\nAdd a concise, obvious README that covers:\n- What Cadence CLI does and why it exists.\n- Supported platforms (macOS, Linux, Windows).\n- Install methods:\n  - macOS: `curl -sSf https://raw.githubusercontent.com/TeamCadenceAI/cadence-cli/main/install.sh | sh`\n  - Linux: same script (with notes about supported distros and prerequisites)\n  - Windows: PowerShell installer script + fallback to manual download\n- Quick start:\n  - `cadence install`\n  - What hooks do\n  - How to verify notes\n- Supported agents (Claude Code, Codex, Cursor, Copilot, Antigravity)\n- Optional GPG encryption overview\n- Links to contributing/security/license\n\nFiles:\n- `/Users/zack/dev/ai-session-commit-linker/README.md`\n\n### 1.2 Add collaborator documentation\nAdd:\n- `CONTRIBUTING.md` with build/test commands (from `CLAUDE.md`), code style, and release process basics.\n- `CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md` using a standard template (Contributor Covenant).\n- `SECURITY.md` with reporting instructions and supported versions.\n\nFiles:\n- `/Users/zack/dev/ai-session-commit-linker/CONTRIBUTING.md`\n- `/Users/zack/dev/ai-session-commit-linker/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md`\n- `/Users/zack/dev/ai-session-commit-linker/SECURITY.md`\n\n## 2. Cross‑Platform Runtime Support\n\n### 2.1 Home directory resolution\nCurrent home detection only uses `HOME`. Update to work on Windows:\n- Use `HOME` if set\n- Else `USERPROFILE`\n- Else `HOMEDRIVE` + `HOMEPATH`\n- Keep Unix behavior unchanged\n\nFile:\n- `/Users/zack/dev/ai-session-commit-linker/src/agents/mod.rs`\n\n### 2.2 Normalize path encoding for Claude Code on Windows\n`encode_repo_path` currently replaces `/` only. On Windows:\n- Replace `\\` with `/` first\n- Replace `:` with `-` to avoid drive letter issues\n- Then replace `/` with `-`\n\nAdd tests for Windows-like paths (string-based; no OS gating needed).\n\nFile:\n- `/Users/zack/dev/ai-session-commit-linker/src/agents/mod.rs`\n\n### 2.3 App data roots for Copilot/Cursor/Antigravity\nAdd helper that maps OS-specific app data roots:\n- macOS: `~/Library/Application Support/<App>`\n- Linux: `~/.config/<App>` or `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/<App>`\n- Windows: `%APPDATA%\\<App>`\n\nUse helper in:\n- Copilot: `Code/User/workspaceStorage`\n- Cursor: `Cursor/User/workspaceStorage` and `~/.cursor/projects`\n- Antigravity: `Antigravity/User/workspaceStorage` + `Antigravity/User`\n\nFiles:\n- `/Users/zack/dev/ai-session-commit-linker/src/agents/copilot.rs`\n- `/Users/zack/dev/ai-session-commit-linker/src/agents/cursor.rs`\n- `/Users/zack/dev/ai-session-commit-linker/src/agents/antigravity.rs`\n- `/Users/zack/dev/ai-session-commit-linker/src/agents/mod.rs` (new helper)\n\n### 2.4 GPG guidance updates\nAdd Windows guidance in `gpg_install_guidance()`:\n- Suggest `winget install GnuPG.GnuPG` (optional)\n- Provide manual download URL text (no raw URLs in code; use phrasing)\n\nFile:\n- `/Users/zack/dev/ai-session-commit-linker/src/main.rs`\n\n## 3. Cross‑Platform Installers\n\n### 3.1 Extend `install.sh` for Linux\nUpdate `install.sh` to:\n- Accept `Darwin` and `Linux`\n- Choose target triples:\n  - macOS: `aarch64-apple-darwin`, `x86_64-apple-darwin`\n  - Linux: `aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu`, `x86_64-unknown