tu-latest` (native)\n  - `aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu` on `ubuntu-latest` (cross)\n- Windows:\n  - `x86_64-pc-windows-msvc` on `windows-latest` (native)\n  - `aarch64-pc-windows-msvc` on `windows-latest` (cross)\n\n### Build Steps\nFor each matrix entry:\n1. `actions/checkout@v4`\n2. `dtolnay/rust-toolchain@stable` with `targets: ${{ matrix.target }}`\n3. For Linux `aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu`:\n   - Add `taiki-e/setup-cross-toolchain-action@v2` (target=aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu)\n4. `cargo build --release --target ${{ matrix.target }}`\n\n### Packaging\n- macOS/Linux:\n  - `target/${{ matrix.target }}/release/cadence`\n  - Create `cadence-cli-${{ matrix.target }}.tar.gz`\n- Windows:\n  - `target/${{ matrix.target }}/release/cadence.exe`\n  - Create `cadence-cli-${{ matrix.target }}.zip` using PowerShell `Compress-Archive`\n\n### Upload\n- `actions/upload-artifact@v4` with `cadence-cli-${{ matrix.target }}` as name\n- Release job downloads artifacts and publishes `.tar.gz` and `.zip`\n\n### Ensure Asset Name Alignment\n- Ensure all filenames match `install.sh` / `install.ps1` expectations:\n  - `cadence-cli-aarch64-apple-darwin.tar.gz`\n  - `cadence-cli-x86_64-apple-darwin.tar.gz`\n  - `cadence-cli-aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu.tar.gz`\n  - `cadence-cli-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu.tar.gz`\n  - `cadence-cli-aarch64-pc-windows-msvc.zip`\n  - `cadence-cli-x86_64-pc-windows-msvc.zip`\n\n## Public Interfaces / Artifacts\n- Release artifacts rename to `cadence-cli-<target>.(tar.gz|zip)`.\n- Binary packaged is `cadence` / `cadence.exe` (matches Cargo `[[bin]]`).\n\n## Test Cases & Scenarios\n1. CI runs `fmt`, `clippy`, and `test` on macOS, Linux, Windows.\n2. Release builds produce 6 artifacts with the exact filenames above.\n3. Windows artifacts unzip to `cadence.exe`; mac/linux tarballs contain `cadence`.\n\n## Assumptions / Defaults\n- Windows ARM64 cross build using `rustup target add aarch64-pc-windows-msvc` on `windows-latest` works without extra SDK steps. If it fails, we’ll 